# Mi Huellita - Configuration

## Environment Variables

Rename this file to `.env` and fill in your Supabase credentials:

```env
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
```

## How to get credentials:

1. Go to https://supabase.com and create a new project
2. Go to Project Settings > API
3. Copy the "Project URL" as SUPABASE_URL
4. Copy the "anon public" key as SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

## Update the frontend:

After updating your .env file, update `js/supabase-client.js` to use these values:

```javascript
const SUPABASE_URL = 'https://your-project.supabase.co';
const SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = 'your-anon-key';
```

Or you can use environment variables in your build process.
